The National Climate Task Force, led by National Climate Advisor Gina McCarthy, held its sixth meeting to discuss President Biden's Build Back Better Agenda. The meeting focused on the President's recent travels to states affected by the climate crisis, highlighting the widespread impact on Americans. The Task Force emphasized the need for an all-of-government approach to help communities prepare, respond, and recover from disasters. The meeting also addressed the urgency of the President's Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal and Build Back Better Agenda in strengthening the nation's resilience to climate change, creating jobs, and growing the economy. The Task Force discussed ways to align the President's priorities across federal agencies to achieve these goals.